cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

The paper presents an automated system based on deep learning for angle-closure detection in AS-OCT images. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The system utilizes a multilevel deep network for learning a discriminative representation from training data, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper involves medical imaging analysis, which could be categorized under the Medical Imaging (cs.MS) sub-category. Additionally, the system utilizes deep features for prediction, which could also suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
